Identify the following rhythm: <image 1>

A. Normal Sinus Rhythm
B. Sinus Tachycardia
C. NSR with PAC'c
D. NSR with 1st Degree AV Block
E. NSR with PVC's
F. Junctional Tachycardia

The rhythm shown in the image is:

B. Sinus Tachycardia

This is characterized by a heart rate that is faster than normal (typically over 100 beats per minute) with regular P waves preceding each QRS complex, indicating that the impulse is originating from the sinus node.
